cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.NA. 

The paper proposes a nonconvex framework for learning low-rank structures from corrupted data, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also introduces optimization algorithms and discusses convergence properties, which are related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Finally, the proposed method is applied to solve two typical problems, which may relate to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
